post_text:
Cornell Faculty and Staff Parade - Monday, June 1 starting at 3:00 pm

The Cornell School District will be conducting a Celebration of Students parade this Monday, June 1. The parade will start at 3:00 pm and will go throughout the Coraopolis and Neville Island communities. Attached to this email is the parade route for you to review! This has been a collaborative effort between the Coraopolis Police and Fire Departments, the Coraopolis Borough, Neville Island Township and Fire Department, as well as Ohio Township Police.

Please encourage your child to step outside and wave to the Cornell faculty and staff as they drive-by and say hello. There will be a police escort, as well as firetrucks and a school bus in the parade. Feel free to have your child makes signs saying hello, but please remember to adhere to social distancing guidelines!

post_text:
Cornell Families:

The Cornell School District is happy to announce the continuation of the Cornell School District’s afterschool PRIDE program, but now in a virtual setting! This program is open for all students in grades 3-8, and we hope this program can provide some fun, enriching activities that kids can do for fun when time allows.

The Cornell School District knows that online, remote learning can be difficult. The goal of moving the PRIDE program to a virtual setting isn’t to, “add more to your plate.” The goal is to provide some engaging and fun activities that students can do at night, or when the weather is bad, and is also a way to continue a sense of normalcy for your children. We wish we could open this up to all students, but unfortunately grant guidelines only allow this to be available for students in grades 3-8. Parents, please be on the lookout in the near future for activities that PRIDE teachers have put together! The program officially will restart on Monday, April 27!

-Cornell Administration

Cornell Families:

Cornell is working with CMU and Meta Mesh, a Pittsburgh-based non-profit, and Coraopolis Community Development Corporation to find creative ways to get students internet access to continue learning through this pandemic. We are looking for community businesses and residents who are willing to consider helping by sharing their internet access in a secure manner. If this is something you are willing to consider, please complete the form below.

http://helpstudentsconnect.cornellsd.org/

post_text:
Cornell Families:

We hope you and your families are well, and that the first week of remote learning is going well. There will be bumps along the way, and we'll work those out together. Continue to communicate with your child's teacher(s) and administration, and adjustments will continue to be made to ensure student's are engaging the best they can through this situation. We appreciate your understanding and flexibility.

Below is a parent resource sheet that outlines all of the different resources available to your students. Contact information is listed in the sheet if you have any questions.

This resource sheet is also posted on the district website on the Coronavirus Update page. Hope you and your family have a great weekend!

post_text:
Cornell Families:

At the beginning of the summer Cornell School District entered into a partnership with a local organization named The Education Partnership. The Education Partnership allowed Cornell teachers to shop for school supplies at their teacher resource warehouse. The Education Partnership is stepping up to help families in need during this COV-19 emergency. The Education Partnership is giving away FREE desktop computers to families who need them. You just need to complete the following Google Form out to be eligible. The first 200 families to fill it out will receive the computers.

An adult family member must fill out the link below in order to receive the computer (IDs will be required at desktop takeout location at Computer Reach located at 1 DRV Drive, Wilkinsburg, PA 15221.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdnqIwqfNqgyFWQG9G8C_S7CKbTS9z2wA3ZR6Hkw3lhMsubdg/viewform?usp=sf_link
